HB 781 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Bourriaque
Abstract: Establishes a fleet registration program created by the Department of Public
Safety and Corrections, office of motor vehicles.
Present law (R.S. 47:508(A)(2)) requires that every automobile or truck registration to be
used as a commercial rental or leased vehicle expire one year from the date of issues and be
renewed annually.
Proposed law retains present law but provides for an exemption to vehicles registered under
the fleet registration program established in proposed law. Further authorizes the vehicles
to be enrolled under an annual or biennial fleet cycle administered by the Dept. of Public
Safety and Corrections (DPS&C), office of motor vehicles (OMV), with proration for partial
annual additions provided in the fleet registration program.
