Proposed law (R.S. 47:508.1(A)) provides for the following definitions:
(1) "Director" defined as the assistant secretary of the DPS&C, OMV.
(2) "Fleet" defined as a group of motor vehicles owned or leased and titled in the name
of a single registered fleet owner, consisting of 10 or more vehicles required to be
registered under present law.
(3) "Registered fleet owner" defined as an entity approved by the OMV under proposed
law to register vehicles as a fleet. Specifies the term includes a leasing or rental
company defined in present law.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:508.1(B)) specifies that for the renewal periods provided in proposed
law, the director must establish a system for the registration of all fleet vehicles owned or
purchased by a registered fleet owner pursuant to proposed law. Further requires the director
establish forms and procedures for initial fleet registration and for periodic updates.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:508.1(C)) specifies that any owner of 10 or more motor vehicles that
is required to be registered under present law and proposed law may apply to be a registered
fleet owner. Specifies that upon approval, the director must issue a unique fleet
identification number to the registered fleet owner. Further authorizes the director to deny,
suspend, or revoke fleet status for noncompliance with proposed law, including failure to
maintain security, failure to remit fees or taxes, the misuse of plates, failure to provide
records, or any other rules adopted by the director pursuant to proposed law.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:508.1(D)) authorizes a registered fleet owner to elect to register its
fleet on an annual or biennial basis in lieu of the standard cycles under. Further requires that
fees for vehicles added after the cycle begins be prorated on a quarterly basis using fractions
of 3/4 of the annual fee for vehicles licensed between July 1st and Sept. 30th, 1/2 of the
annual fee for vehicles licensed between Oct. 1st and Dec. 31st, and 1/4 of the annual fee for
vehicles licensed on or after Jan. 1st. Requires an additional full annual fee be added to the
partial annual prorated fee when a biennial registration is sought to add vehicles mid-cycle.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:508.1(E)) requires that vehicles subject to La. safety inspection
requirements comply prior to issuance or renewal as applicable. Further requires that for
rental or leased fleet vehicles, a valid inspection sticker or inspection certification remain
effective for the duration of the rental or lease term. Additionally requires that reinspection
or issuance of a new brake tag not be required during that period. Additionally specifies that
the director may authorize electronic proof of inspection in fleet application.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:508.1(F)) requires a registered fleet owner maintain proof of financial
responsibility meeting the Motor Vehicle Safety Responsibility Law. Requires that the
rental companies allocation of primary and secondary coverage be as provided in present
law, and the definitions applicable to vehicle rental insurers be as provided in present law.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:508.1(G)) authorizes the director to issue a unique fleet license plate
or validation device for vehicles in a registered fleet. Further allows registration plates to
be transferred among vehicles within the fleet subject to reporting and audit controls.
Further requires that unassigned plate inventory be secured and reconciled in accordance
with the rules adopted by the director.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:508.1(H)) requires that automobiles, vans, and sport utility vehicles
used as commercial rental or daily leased vehicles be issued plates in accordance with the
DPS&C, OMV, policies or rules governing commercial plate classifications, including any
successor classifications.
Proposed law (R.S. 47:508.1(I)) requires the director provide technical specifications for
secure electronic data exchange to support daily or periodic fleet registration updates, title
